<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/World-fisheries-must-prepare-for-climate-change" title="World fisheries must prepare for climate change " alt="link">World fisheries must prepare for climate change </a></h2>

	
					<p>The fishing industry and national fisheries authorities must do more to understand and prepare for the impacts that climate change will have on world fisheries, says a new FAO report published on the 2nd of March. According to the latest edition of the UN agency's The State of World Fisheries and Aquaculture (SOFIA), existing responsible fishing practices need to be more widely implemented and current management plans should be expanded to include strategies for coping with climate change. Read the report <a href="http://www.fao.org/docrep/011/i0250e/i0250e00.htm" target="_blank">The State of World Fisheries and Aquaculture</a> (Source: FAO, 2 March 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">24/03/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/World-fisheries-must-prepare-for-climate-change">Read more...</a>
