<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Agriculture-Future-Scenarios-for-Southern-Africa-The-Livestock-Sector-in-Zambia-and-Rising-Food-Prices" title="Agriculture: Future Scenarios for Southern Africa – The Livestock Sector in Zambia and Rising Food Prices" alt="link">Agriculture: Future Scenarios for Southern Africa – The Livestock Sector in Zambia and Rising Food Prices</a></h2>

	
					<p>By Humphrey Mulemba, IISD, 2009. The briefing aims to explore the forces of rising food prices and their impact on Zambia’s livestock sector. The agriculture, in particular the livestock, sector is critical to the alleviation of poverty in the country although serious livestock diseases have intermittently hit the livestock industry for more than two decades.</p>
							<p><span class="date">24/03/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Agriculture-Future-Scenarios-for-Southern-Africa-The-Livestock-Sector-in-Zambia-and-Rising-Food-Prices">Read more...</a>
