						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Standard-bearers-Horticultural-exports-and-private-standards-in-Africa" title="Standard bearers: Horticultural exports and private standards in Africa " alt="link">Standard bearers: Horticultural exports and private standards in Africa </a></h2>

	
					<p>By Adeline Borot de Battisti, James MacGregor, Andrew Graffham, February 2009. Private standards are set by the food producing industry and retailers, mainly to assure food safety and good agricultural practice. However their proliferation is a major concern in developing countries where these standards are regarded as too expensive for smallholders to comply with. So what really are the benefits and costs of private standards for small-scale producers? This publication presents state-of-the-art research and analysis to explore the issues surrounding smallholders, private standards, and exports from Africa.</p>
							<p><span class="date">24/03/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Standard-bearers-Horticultural-exports-and-private-standards-in-Africa">Read more...</a>
