					<p>African Drought Risk and Development Network (ADDN) is focused on promoting applied exchange of experience on key issues linking drought risk and development; providing a platform for the development and dissemination of good practice &amp; tools; is a bridge to various resources &amp; opportunities in Africa and beyond; and acts as a Forum for the elaboration of quality and policy relevant collective practice on drought risk management.</p>
